claim.claim-text:
A self-closing slide rail assembly (10), comprising:
a first rail (12);
a second rail (14) longitudinally displaceable relative to the first rail (12), the second rail (14) comprising a guide portion (20) and a stop portion (22) close to the guide portion (20), the guide portion (20) and the stop portion (22) defining a first positioning groove (26) therebetween; and
the self-closing mechanism (16) according to claim 1, the self-closing mechanism (16) being mounted on the first rail (12), wherein the movable member (46) further comprises a second projection (80), the second projection (80) being movable along the first edge (58) of the housing (40); the movable member (46) has a first side (74) and a second side (76) opposite the first side (74), the first projection (78) and the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) being located on the first side (74); the housing (40) has a longitudinal portion (50) and a transverse portion (54) connected to the longitudinal portion (50), the first edge (58) of the housing (40) being substantially parallel to the longitudinal portion (50), the elastic member (44) being located in the longitudinal portion (50), the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) corresponding to the transverse portion (54); and the self-closing mechanism (16) further comprises an actuating portion (47) connected to the second side (76) of the movable member (46);
wherein when the actuating portion (47) of the self-closing mechanism (16) is engaged in the first positioning groove (26) of the second rail (14) and the second rail (14) is displaced relative to the first rail (12) from a retracted position toward an extended position, the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) is moved from the first edge (58) to the second edge (60) and enters into engagement with the engaging portion (42), and the elastic member (44) of the self-closing mechanism (16) stores elastic energy; and when the second rail (14) is displaced relative to the first rail (12) from the extended position toward the retracted position, the guide portion (20) of the second rail (14) guides the actuating portion (47) of the self-closing mechanism (16) into engagement with the first positioning groove (26) of the second rail (14) such that the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) leaves the engaging portion (42) and, as the elastic member (44) of the self-closing mechanism (16) releases the elastic energy, is moved from the second edge (60) to the first edge (58), the movable member (46) thus driving the second rail (14) back to the retracted position automatically.

A self-closing slide rail assembly (10), comprising:
a first rail (12);
a second rail (14) longitudinally displaceable relative to the first rail (12), the second rail (14) comprising a guide portion (20) and a stop portion (22) close to the guide portion (20), the guide portion (20) and the stop portion (22) defining a first positioning groove (26) therebetween; and
the self-closing mechanism (16) according to claim 1, the self-closing mechanism (16) being mounted on the first rail (12);
wherein when the actuating portion (47) of the self-closing mechanism (16) is engaged in the first positioning groove (26) of the second rail (14) and the second rail (14) is displaced relative to the first rail (12) from a retracted position toward an extended position, the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) is moved from the first edge (58) to the second edge (60) and enters into engagement with the engaging portion (42), and the elastic member (44) of the self-closing mechanism (16) stores elastic energy; and when the second rail (14) is displaced relative to the first rail (12) from the extended position toward the retracted position, the guide portion (20) of the second rail (14) guides the actuating portion (47) of the self-closing mechanism (16) into engagement with the first positioning groove (26) of the second rail (14) such that the second projection (80) of the movable member (46) leaves the engaging portion (42) and, as the elastic member (44) of the self-closing mechanism (16) releases the elastic energy, is moved from the second edge (60) to the first edge (58), the movable member (46) thus driving the second rail (14) back to the retracted position automatically.
